Privacy Policy

Daily Helper App

Last updated:  2/19/2026

Daily Helper App (“the App”) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how the App handles user information.

1. Information We Collect
Daily Helper App does not collect, store, transmit, or share any personal information.

The App:
Does not require user accounts.

Does not collect names, emails, phone numbers, or locations.

Does not use analytics services.

Does not use advertising services.

Does not track user activity.


2. Local Data Storage
All data entered into the App (such as expense entries, selected currency, and theme preference) is stored locally on your device only using secure local storage.

This data:
Never leaves your device.

Is not transmitted to any server.

Is not accessible by the developer.

Is deleted if the App is uninstalled.


3. Internet Usage
The App does not require internet access to function.
The only time a browser may open is when you voluntarily tap:

Privacy Policy

Terms of Service


These links open in your device’s default browser.

4. Third-Party Services

Daily Helper App does not use:

Advertising SDKs

Analytics tools

Tracking technologies

Cloud storage services

5. Data Security
Since all information is stored locally on your device, data security depends on your device’s own security measures.

6. Children’s Privacy
Daily Helper App does not knowingly collect personal information from children or any users.

7. Changes to This Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated if the App’s functionality changes. Any updates will be reflected on this page with a revised date.

8. Contact
If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, you may contact:
